Consists of static methods across four class:

0. Methods
  * **All** methods of class (inherited, overridden)
  * Easily acquire a `MethodHandle` (works in Java 8, 9 and 10)
0. Names
  * Class names to/from binary, descriptor and resource
0. Resources
  * Get the bytecode for a class, 
  * Find a class' location
0. Types
  * Methods typically overloaded to accept `java.lang.Class`, `java.lang.reflect.Type` and `java.lang.String`
  * _isA_ methods for primitive, primitive-wrapper, interface and class
  * Find all interfaces/supertypes
  * Convert primitives to/from wrappers
  * `requiresInterface`/`requiresClass` argument checkers

